<ss1>
<st>
 Career </st>

<p>

In 1947, Martin Balsam was selected by <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../874/42874.xml">
Elia Kazan</link></actor>
</person>
 and <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../438/572438.xml">
Lee Strasberg</link></actor>
 to be a player in the <it><school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.8">
<educational_institution wordnetid="108276342" confidence="0.8">
<institution wordnetid="108053576" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../560/437560.xml">
Actors Studio</link></institution>
</educational_institution>
</school>
</it> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../831/29831.xml">
television</link> program.  He went on to appear in a number of television plays in the 1950s and returned frequently to television as a guest star on numerous dramas (e.g., <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../389/1409389.xml">
The Twilight Zone</link></series>
</it> and <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../610/247610.xml">
Alfred Hitchcock Presents</link></series>
</it>). Balsam appeared in such films as <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../361/42361.xml">
On the Waterfront</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../605/92605.xml">
12 Angry Men</link></movie>
</it> (as Juror #1), <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../909/10090909.xml">
Time Limit</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../880/23880.xml">
Psycho</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../029/171029.xml">
Cape Fear</link></movie>
</it> (1962) as the police chief,  <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../906/51906.xml">
Breakfast at Tiffany's</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../431/297431.xml">
Seven Days in May</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../822/3834822.xml">
Hombre</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../560/3628560.xml">
Catch-22</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../018/58018.xml">
Tora! Tora! Tora!</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../409/955409.xml">
The Taking of Pelham One Two Three</link></movie>
</it>, <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../929/12009929.xml">
Two-Minute Warning</link></movie>
